<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 is composed of three principal summits. The highest point is the Grand Pic de la Meije at 3,984 metres. The Doigt de Dieu (English: Finger of God), a large snow-clad tower at the east end of the ridge, overhanging the south slopes, is an attraction for mountaineers of all levels of ability. The first ascent of 
<REF ID="323.5" SEMCAT="mountain" SYNCAT="np-obj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">La Meije</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
